Step 5: Personalization and Output
Store user preferences (keywords, topics, sentiment) in a config or database.

Present summaries in a simple GUI (Tkinter) or web app (Flask/Streamlit).

Optionally, add keyword extraction using BERT or spaCy for more advanced filtering.â€‹

Example Workflow
User enters preferred topics and news sources.

Script fetches latest articles, filters by user preferences.

Summarizes filtered articles and displays concise summaries.
